reviewText: I loved the scenery in the movie, and the portrayal of the Cuban people. Makes me want to go see Cuba for myself. The acting and the storyline, however, were terrible! All it needed was Elvira narrating from the side, to spruce it up!
Had a little bit of an unexpected twist. I only watched it because it starred Greg Wise whom I haven't seen anything new of in sometime.
You'll like this one.
Unusual but very nice surprise ending.

Started slow and appeared to be predictable and cliche. However, I am happy I stayed the course. I realized that I liked and cared about the protagonist enough to compel me to continue watching. I'm glad I remained engaged in the film. It has some piquant moments that resonated with me and left an impression; a rare thing in my experience. I watched this film on impulse based upon its cover art, without reading the synopsis and without any expectations. I was entertained. Well done!
